page.title: 16Garages and Transport
page.content:
There are five garages in the area.One at Five Ash Down J.T.Brayley, four at and near Maresfield,Maresfield Garage,Chichester Caravans,Chevron and Chequers service station.They all sell different makes of petrol.Most sell sweets,drinks and other foods .One sells caravans and one sells petrol only.Two garages do car repairs and M.O.T tests.In our area we have lots of transport because of the By_Pass and A272 and A22.On the By_Pass there are earthmovers,diggers,bulldozers etc.Other than that there are cars,lorries,motorbikes,bicyles.There are also buses.An average of twenty buses go through Maresfield and twenty through Five Ash Down each day.
By Jonathan and Matthew.
